<p>Dear Mother<br/>We are working hard loading transports There are lots of French and English<br/>soldiers here. I am prettty well. This is a P.C. issued to the French troops for<br/>use at the Front. love to Jim and Paddy and yourself.<br/>Best love to all, your loving son Arthur  XXXXXXXXXXXXXX<br/>There are Zouaves and Turkos here and all sorts of French uniforms. The<br/>town is alive with soldiers. My letters may be irregular after this as we do not<br/>know when we may move. a lot have gone</p>
